body:
This was not a buff. I know it was intended as one, but it was not thought through. Did you forget how terrible you made her Q? It doesn&#039;t even hit anymore because you can&#039;t keep up with people. 

With that change you just took something reliable - the speed buff that a lot of people actually made use of - and replaced it with a possible reward for not killing a target. In the end this was far from a buff, because now Evelynn misses more Q&#039;s than usual and she has a lot less tools in combat once she shows herself. 

Not only you made her a weaker fighter, but you also made her more binary and plain. Since she has no gapcloser, she had to rely on her dash to go in/break slows/get out and it was a tricky spell to use, but there was also a hidden strength that SEPARATED GOOD EVES FROM THE GREAT which was the passive part. At full stacks you could manoeuvre around people and dodge a lot of damage - which is basically using both your game knowledge AND skill to a great effect. 

Why would you remove this mechanic and replace it with a dumb reset, especially when she already had a reset on kill/assist anyway?

EDIT: 
@Riot
@Meddler
@Statikk
@SorryIfIdidntmentionyou
Thank you for looking into this (even if it wasn't because of this particular thread)!
Rito delivers!
